ame=religion>{{cite news|last1=Kane|first1=Paul|title=Rep. Michael Grimm, facing federal charges, surrenders to FBI|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/rep-michael-grimm-facing-federal-charges-will-surrender-to-fbi-sources-say/2014/04/27/fd302426-ce33-11e3-b812-0c92213941f4_story.html|accessdate=July 24, 2014|publisher=Washington Post|date=April 28, 2014}}</ref>\n|website      = [http://www.grimmforcongress.com/ Campaign website]<br>[http://www.grimm.house.gov/ Rep. Grimm]\n|allegiance   = {{flag|United States}}\n|branch       = {{flag|United States Marine Corps}}\n|serviceyears = 1989\u20131990; 1990\u20131991 (active)<br />1990; 1991\u20131997 (reserve)\n|rank         = [[Image:USMC-E4.svg|25px]] [[Corporal#United States Marine Corps|Corporal]]\n|unit         = [[File:Marine Forces Reserve insignia (transparent background).png|25px]] [[United States Marine Corps Reserve|U.S. Marine Corps Reserve]]\n|battles      = [[Gulf War|Persian Gulf War]]<br>{{*}}[[Operation Desert Shield (Gulf War)|Operation Desert Shield]]<br>{{*}}[[Operation Desert Storm]]\n|awards       = [[Image:Combat Action Ribbon.svg|23px|border]] [[Combat Action Ribbon]]<br />[[File:Navy Unit Commendation ribbon.svg|23px|border]] [[Navy Unit Commendation]]<br />[[Image:Navy Meritorious Unit Commendation ribbon.svg|23px|border]] [[Meritorious Unit Commendation]]\n}}\n\n'''Michael Gerard Grimm''' (born February 7, 1970)<ref name=CQ>{{cite web|title=Rep. Michael G. Grimm (R-N.Y.)|url=http://www.rollcall.com/members/32707.html|website=Roll Call|publisher=Congressional Quarterly|accessdate=July 24, 2014}}</ref> is the  [[United States Representative]] for {{ushr|NY|11}}, serving since 2011. Numbered as the [[New York's 13th congressional district|13th District]] during his first term, the district consists of [[Staten Island]] and parts of [[Brooklyn]]. Grimm is a member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]] and is the only Republican representing a significant portion of [[New York City]]. He is a former [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] agent, businessman, attorney, and [[United States Marine Corps|U.S. Marine]], having served in the [[Gulf War|Persian Gulf War]].\n\nOn April 28, 2014, Grimm was charged with a 20-count indictment by federal authorities for fraud, federal tax evasion, and perjury.<ref name=\"Clifford\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/29/nyregion/representative-michael-grimm-is-indicted-on-fraud-charges.html|title=Grimm, Staten Island Congressman, Is Indicted on Fraud Charges|last=Clifford|first=Stephanie|publisher=New York Times|date=April 29, 2014}}</ref> On December 23, 2014 he pleaded guilty to a single count of felony tax fraud, and \"acknowledged committing perjury, hiring illegal immigrants and committing wire fraud.\"<ref>http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/24/nyregion/rep-michael-grimm-pleads-guilty-to-tax-fraud.html?_r=0</ref>  After initially vowing to retain his seat, Grimm announced on December 30, 2014 that he would resign from Congress on January 5, 2015, just before the next Congress convenes.<ref name=BBC>{{cite web|title=Michael Grimm: NY Congressman resigns after guilty plea|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-30636320|website=BBC News|publisher=|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> There will be [[New York's 11th congressional district special election, 2015|a special election]] to replace him.\n\n==Early life and education==\nGrimm was raised as a Catholic in [[Queens, New York]], the son of Petrina (n\u00e9e Castronova) and Gerard Grimm. He is of German, Irish, and Sicilian descent.<ref name=fairytale>{{cite web|author=Staten Island Advance/Jan Somma-Hammel|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/11/grimm_living_his_fairy_tale.html|title=Michael Grimm, now congressman-elect, is living his fairy tale|publisher=SILive.com|date=November 4, 2010|accessdate=July 15, 2014}}</ref> He graduated from [[Archbishop Molloy High School]] in 1988.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Barnard|first1=Anne|title=Rising G.O.P. Star From Staten Island Draws on Political Gifts to Fend Off Critics|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/09/nyregion/michael-grimm-gop-congressman-fights-critics.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0|accessdate=July 3, 2014|publisher=New York Times|date=March 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\nGrimm entered active duty with the [[United States Marine Corps|U.S. Marine Corps]] in 1989. In 1990, he was deployed overseas as part of the [[6th Communication Battalion]]. He received a combat promotion to [[corporal]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.combatveteransforcongress.org/cand/60|title=Electing Fiscal Conservatives|publisher=Combat Veterans For Congress|date=June 24, 2014|accessdate=July 15, 2014}}</ref> and was awarded the [[Combat Action Ribbon]], [[Navy Unit Commendation]], the [[Meritorious Unit Commendation]], among other awards. {{citation needed|date=November 2014}}\n\nGrimm received a [[BBA]] in [[accounting]] from [[Baruch College]] in 1994. He transferred to the U.S. Marine Corps Reserve and was discharged from service in 1997.<ref name=\"Vets\">{{cite web|url=http://combatveteransforcongress.org/cand/60 |title=Congressman Michael Grimm|publisher=Combat Veterans for Congress |date= |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> He received a [[Juris Doctor]] ''([[magna cum laude]]'') from [[New York Law School]] in 2002.<ref>{{cite news|first=Alicia|last=Colon|title=Inexplicable behavior by the Island GOP chairman|date=June 6, 2010|url=http://www.silive.com/opinion/columns/index.ssf/2010/06/inexplicable_behavior_by_the_i.html|work=SILive.com|accessdate=January 29, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Federal Bureau of Investigation (1991\u20132006)===\nGrimm entered the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] as a clerk in 1991. In 1995, he entered the [[FBI Academy]] in [[Quantico Station, Virginia]]. He graduated as a [[Special Agent|special agent]] and was certified to become an [[undercover agent]]. He transitioned into undercover agent work, eventually working in the FBI [[Gambino crime family|Gambino]] Squad and was responsible for learning about the inside activities of [[Peter Gotti]], [[John Gotti]]'s brother.<ref name=\"nydailynews1\">{{cite web|last=Saltonstall|first=David|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/2009/11/15/2009-11-15_fbis_mikey_suits_aims_for_congress_exundercover_mafia_buster_seeks_si_seat.html|title=Ex-undercover Mafia buster, Michael 'Mikey Suits' Grimm, seeks Staten Island congressional seat|publisher=New York Daily News|date=November 14, 2009|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> Grimm worked for the FBI as an agent for 9 years.\n\nIn 2011, [[Evan Ratliff]], writing for ''[[The New Yorker]]'', reported that Grimm had been the subject of an internal investigation into allegations he abused his authority as a FBI agent in a nightclub in 1999.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ratliff|first=Evan|title=The Mark: The F.B.I. Needs Informants, but What Happens When They Go Too Far?|date=May 2, 2011|publisher=New Yorker|url=http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2011/05/02/110502fa_fact_ratliff?currentPage=all|accessdate=January 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ratliff|first=Evan|url=http://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/newsdesk/2011/04/congressman-michael-grimm-at-the-caribbean-tropics.html|title=Congressman Grimm and the Night Club|publisher=The New Yorker|date=April 29, 2011|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> At the time of ''The New Yorker'' report, the New York Police Department and U.S. Justice Department had not released documents regarding the alleged incident. Grimm stated that the incident had been fully investigated and that he had been cleared of all allegations.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tracy|first=Thomas|url=http://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/34/18/all_grimmdeblasio_2011_5_6_bk.html|title=DeBlasio to Grimm: Come clean about 1999 bar fight|publisher=The Brooklyn Paper|date=April 28, 2011|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Ben|url=http://www.politico.com/blogs/bensmith/0411/The_FBI_agent_and_the_night_club.html|title=The FBI agent and the night club|publisher=Politico|date=April 25, 2011|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nDuring his time with the FBI, Grimm spent two years posing as a small cap stocks broker, uncovering white-collar criminals on [[Wall Street]].<ref name=\"nydailynews1\"/> According to Grimm, the firm was involved in [[money laundering]], making false trades, and manipulating stocks.<ref name=\"foxnews1\">{{cite news| url=http://nation.foxnews.com/rep-michael-grimm/2011/01/19/meet-undercover-fbi-agent-turned-freshman-congressman | work=Fox News | title=Meet the Undercover FBI Agent-Turned-Freshman Congressman \u2013 Rep. Michael Grimm \u2013 Fox Nation | date=January 19, 2011}}</ref> After building a strong case for two years, he and the firm's partners were arrested together, at which point, the police informed the group that they had been infiltrated by an undercover agent.<ref name=\"foxnews1\"/> Grimm stated in 2011 that he has long been aware of the possibility that people may try to take revenge on him.<ref>{{cite web|last=Heil |first=Emily |url=http://www.rollcall.com/issues/56_66/-202382-1.html |title=Threats Not New for Former Lawmen |publisher=Roll Call |date=January 12, 2011 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> He left the FBI in 2006, citing his exhaustion from working long hours.<ref name=\"Randall\">{{cite web|last=Randall |first=Judy L. |url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/07/gulf_war_vet_former_fbi_agent.html |title=Gulf War vet, former FBI agent has 'a burning desire to serve' |publisher=Staten Island Advance |date=July 11, 2010 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Business and finance (2006\u20132010)===\nBefore joining the FBI, Grimm worked for a year for Whale Securities,<ref name=\"ties\">{{cite news|last1=Cowan|first1=Alison Leigh|last2=Barnard|first2=Anne|last3=Rashbaum|first3=William K.|title=Congressman's Business Ties Are at Odds with Upright Image|date=February 15, 2012|accessdate=September 18, 2013|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/16/nyregion/michael-grimms-business-ties-are-at-odds-with-upright-image.html|publisher=N.Y. Times}}</ref> an investment banking firm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Company Overview of Whale Securities Co., L.P.|publisher=Bloomberg Businessweek|accessdate=September 18, 2013|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=1062802}}</ref> Shortly before leaving the bureau, Grimm invested in Texas luxury real estate with former agent Carlos Luquis.<ref name=\"ties\"/>\n\nIn 2006, Grimm founded a small [[health food restaurant]] called Healthalicious in [[Manhattan, New York|Manhattan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whorunsgov.com/Profiles/Michael_Grimm|title=Michael Grimm (R-N.Y.)|publisher=Whorunsgov.com|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> He co-owned and served as principal and [[chief executive officer]] of Austin Refuel Transport, an [[Austin, Texas]]-based [[bio-fuel]] company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grimm.house.gov/about-me/full-biography|title=About Me: Full Biography|publisher=Grimm.house.gov|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> As of 2011, Grimm owned 28% of the company, although he is no longer involved in daily operations nor is he CEO. In July 2011, the ''[[New York Daily News]]'' reported that Austin Refuel Transport had received eleven safety violations in two [[U.S. Department of Transportation]] checkups.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-07-17/news/29800917_1_grimm-safety-violations-biodiesel|location=New York|work=Daily News|title=Holiday shopping: Tips to find the best deals on Cyber Monday 2010|first=Benjamin|last=Lesser|date=July 17, 2011}}</ref> Grimm\u2019s spokesman said that he now \"has no authority or managerial role in the daily activities of the company. He is simply a silent investor.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lesser|first1=Benjamin|title=Rep. Michael Grimm's trucking business racks up toxic safety violations, raises interest questions|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/rep-michael-grimm-trucking-business-racks-toxic-safety-violations-raises-interest-questions-article-1.162227|accessdate=July 3, 2014|publisher=New York Daily News|date=July 17, 2011}}</ref>\n\n===U.S. House of Representatives (2011\u20132014)===\n\n====Elections====\n;2010\n{{See also|United States House of Representatives elections in New York, 2010#District 13*}}\nGrimm launched his campaign for the 13th New York Congressional District seat on January 23, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wrobleski|first=Tom|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/01/republican_michael_grimm_launc.html|title=Republican Michael Grimm launches campaign against McMahon on Staten Island|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=January 23, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> Grimm was endorsed by former [[NYC mayor]] [[Rudy Giuliani]] as well as [[Guy Molinari]], a former U.S. Representative and [[Staten Island]] [[Borough President]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/02/former_mayor_rudy_giuliani_to.html |title=Former Mayor Rudy Giuliani to endorse GOP congressional candidate Michael Grimm|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=February 18, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> He was also endorsed by the [[Conservative Party of New York State]]. He was challenged by Michael Allegretti who was endorsed by former six term U.S. Representative [[Vito Fossella]], the [[Staten Island]] Republican Party,<ref>{{cite web |last=Saltonstall |first=David |title= Staten Island GOP Committee Endorses Michael Allegretti for Vito Fossella's Old Congressional Seat |date= May 28, 2010 |publisher= N.Y. Daily News |url= http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/staten-island-gop-committee-endorses-michael-allegretti-vito-fossella-old-congressional-seat-article-1.449479}}</ref> State Senator [[Andrew Lanza]], and State Assemblyman [[Lou Tobacco]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Wroblewski|first=Tom|title=Allegretti Collects Endorsements from Lanza and Tobacco|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=June 4, 2010|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/06/allegretti_collects_endorsemen.html}}</ref> Allegretti worked for the nonprofit [[Climate Group]] and cited his relationships with NYC Mayor [[Michael R. Bloomberg]] and former [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|British Prime Minister]] [[Tony Blair]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Hernandez|first=Raymond|title= The City: Fight for Staten Island|publisher=New York Times|date=October 23, 2009|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/25/nyregion/25bcongressmb.html?_r=0}}</ref> Grimm chose not to even contest the Staten Island's party endorsement because of their \u201ccorrupt political culture\u201d and \u201csham convention.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Slajda|first=Rachel|title=Staten Island GOP, Deprived of Fossella, Chooses Allegretti|date=May 28, 2010|publisher=TPM|url=http://tpmdc.talkingpointsmemo.com/2010/05/staten-island-gop-deprived-of-fossella-chooses-allegretti.php}}</ref>\n\nGrimm's primary win was divisive for the Republican Party leadership, which was more in favor of Allegretti.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wrobleski|first=Tom|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/10/staten_island_gops_endorsement.html|title=Staten Island GOP's endorsement of Grimm is less than resounding|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=October 6, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> His campaign gained national attention from the Tea Party and the National Republican Congressional Committee, which contributed $90,000 to Grimm's campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailycaller.com/2010/10/21/thedc-interview-republican-new-york-congressional-candidate-michael-grimm|title=TheDC Interview: Republican New York congressional candidate Michael Grimm|publisher=Daily Caller|date=October 21, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> He received endorsements from high profile Republicans, including Rudy Giuliani,<ref>{{cite web|first=Peter N.|last=Spencer|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/10/giuliani_buoys_grimm_at_whiteh.html|title=Giuliani buoys Grimm at Whitehall Ferry Terminal|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=October 29, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> [[John McCain]], [[Sarah Palin]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Chen|first=David W.|title=Results Are Mixed for Tea Party in New York|date=September 15, 2010|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/09/15/nyregion/15nytea.html|publisher=New York Times}}(coverage of the Grimm vs. McMahon race)</ref> and former President [[George H.W. Bush]], who applauded his service in the Gulf War.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wrobleski|first=Tom|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/10/former_president_george_bush_e.html|title=Former President George Bush endorses Michael Grimm|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=October 9, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nGrimm faced incumbent [[Michael McMahon]] in the general election. On October 12, the ''Staten Island Advance'' reported that it had been receiving emails from the McMahon campaign attacking Grimm's business credentials.<ref>{{cite web|first=Judy L.|last=Randall|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/10/mcmahon_peppers_advance_with_e.html|title=Staten Island Rep. McMahon peppers Advance with e-mails that rip Grimm|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=October 12, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> The emails claimed that Grimm's real estate and restaurant investments were failures despite Grimm's repeated insistences that they were successful.<ref>{{cite web|last=Patten|first=David A.|date=October 24, 2010|title=2010: Democrats Set Records for Dirtiest Election Ever|publisher=Newsmax|url=http://www.newsmax.com/Newsfront/campaign-dirty-tricks-tea/2010/10/24/id/374719}}</ref> Grimm reportedly admitted in an interview with the ''[[Staten Island Advance]]'' newspaper that his former restaurant in Manhattan, Healthalicious, had been on the verge of bankruptcy, forcing him to sell his stake in it.<ref name=\"Randall\"/> A major difference between the two candidates was the issue of the U.S. economic stimulus package, which the ''[[Staten Island Advance]]'' said was the \"starkest contrast\" among the two candidates. Grimm stated that the stimulus was a \"huge waste\" of taxpayer money and was ineffective in generating job creation and economic recovery, whereas McMahon cited improvements in the state budget and renovations on the Staten Island Expressway and the Saint George Ferry Terminal as direct successes of the stimulus.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wrobleski|first=Tom|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/10/stimulus_a_political_football.html|title=Stimulus dollars become political football in Staten Island congressional race|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=October 11, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn November 2, 2010, Grimm defeated McMahon in the race by 51%\u201348%. The ''Staten Island Advance'' reported that Grimm won in large part due to his political signs, which became popular among his supporters. They stated, \"McMahon raised my property taxes 18.5%\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Wrobleski |first=Tom |url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/11/tax_signs_may_have_helped_prop.html|title='Tax signs' may have helped propel Michael Grimm to victory in Staten Island congressional race|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=November 8, 2010|accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n;2012\n{{See also|United States House of Representatives elections in New York, 2012#District 11}}\nAfter redistricting, Grimm's district was renumbered as the 11th District.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2011/02/staten_island_rep_michael_grim_1.html|title=Staten Island Rep. Michael Grimm: This is your life|date=February 28, 2011|accessdate=April 21, 2011|work=[[Staten Island Advance]]|first=Judy L.|last=Randall}}</ref> He was challenged by Democrat Mark Murphy, a former [[personal assistant|aide]] to [[New York City Public Advocate]] [[Bill de Blasio]]. Grimm won re-election to a second term 53%\u201346%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.com/2012-election/map/#/House/2012/NY|title=2014 Election Results Senate: Live Map by State, Midterm Midterm Races Races|publisher=Politico|accessdate=July 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\n;2014\n{{See also|United States House of Representatives elections in New York, 2014#District 11}}\nGrimm was elected to a third term.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wrobleski|first=Tom|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2014/02/staten_islands_rep_michael_gri_8.html|title=Timeline: Staten Island's Rep. Michael Grimm elected and re-elected, but dogged by allegations (w/photos)|publisher=Staten Island Advance|date=February 1, 2014|accessdate=February 5, 2014}}</ref> He received the backing of the Staten Island Republican party and the Independence Party, who called him \u201c\u2018a truly independent voice\u2019 for his constituents.\u201d<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wrobleski|first1=Tom|title=Staten Island GOP Rep. Michael Grimm gets backing of state Independence Party in re-election bid|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2014/03/staten_island_gop_rep_michael_3.html|accessdate=September 2, 2014|publisher=SILive|date=March 4, 2014}}</ref>\n\nGrimm faced [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] nominee [[Domenic Recchia]] in the general election. Grimm was endorsed by the Association of Flight Attendants-CWA, the International Union of Painters and Allied Trades, the United Transportation Union, and the Humane Society Legislative Fund.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Barkan|first1=Ross|title=Michael Grimm Nets a Rare Endorsement|url=http://observer.com/2014/10/michael-grimm-nets-a-rare-endorsement|accessdate=October 15, 2014|publisher=New York Observer|date=October 2, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Wrobleski|first1=Tom|title=Sparks fly as Recchia, Grimm pick up endorsements in House race|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2014/10/sparks_fly_as_recchia_grimm_pi.html|accessdate=October 15, 2014|publisher=Staten Island Live|date=October 14, 2014}}</ref>\nGrimm defeated Recchia on election night, November 5, 2014.\n\n====Tenure====\nDuring an interview of all freshmen Republican members with Sean Hannity, Congressman-elect Grimm took exception to being asked if he was a conservative. He replied that he was \"American first\" and that \"we have become way too polarized,\" indicating a desire for compromise with Democrats.<ref>FoxNews.com, [http://video.foxnews.com/v/4485122/hannitys-freshmen-focus-group/ Hannity's Freshman Focus Group], January 4, 2011, at 5:30 mark</ref> Grimm did not join the [[Tea Party Caucus]] within the House, and instead joined the more moderate [[Republican Main Street Partnership]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Freedlander |first=David |url=http://www.observer.com/2011/politics/ny-tea-partiers-join-moderate-gop-caucus |title=NY Tea Partiers Join 'Moderate' G.O.P. Caucus |publisher=The New York Observer |date=January 28, 2011 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n=====Fiscal issues=====\nGrimm was appointed to the [[United States House Committee on Financial Services|House Financial Services Committee]], which the ''Staten Island Advance'' observed as a major opportunity for Grimm to impact the debate on financial reform. Roughly 70,000 of his constituents were involved in financial services, making this a vital issue for his political profile.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/12/staten_islands_grimm_lands_spo.html |title=Staten Island's Grimm lands spot on House Financial Services Committee |publisher=Staten Island Advance |date=December 10, 2010 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nGrimm introduced legislation that would require potential whistleblowers to report wrongdoing to their employers before reporting it to the Securities and Exchange Commission if they want to receive a cash reward from the SEC.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.marketwatch.com/story/republicans-take-aim-at-whistleblower-rule-2011-05-11?link=MW_latest_news|title= Republicans take aim at whistleblower rule|author= Kate Shepherd|date= May 11, 2011 |work= MarketWatch|publisher= Medill News Service|accessdate=May 13, 2011}}</ref>\n\nGrimm voted for the fiscal cliff compromise bill that permanently extended most of the Bush tax cuts.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Weigel|first1=Dave|title=So, Which Republicans Voted for the Fiscal Cliff Deal?|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/weigel/2013/01/02/so_which_republicans_voted_for_the_fiscal_cliff_deal.html|accessdate=September 2, 2014|publisher=Slate|date=January 2, 2013}}</ref>\n\n=====Gun control=====\nFollowing the [[2011 Tucson shooting|shooting of Gabrielle Giffords]] in 2011, Grimm voiced support for \"security-based situational awareness training\", including how to spot suspicious people, when to run for an exit, and how to keep guards at close range. Grimm also said congressmen should consider carrying firearms. House Leader [[John Boehner]] called his suggestions an \"excellent idea\" and indicated that security would be a major focus for Congress in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|first=Natalie |last=O'Neill |url=http://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/34/3/br_grimmsecurity_2011_1_21_bk.html?comm=1 |title=Grimm: House members should pack heat if they want |publisher=The Brooklyn Paper |date=January 14, 2011 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n=====Abortion=====\nGrimm voted in favor of the Pain-Capable Unborn Child Protection Act, a bill banning abortions after the 20th week of fertilization.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Eilperin|first1=Juliet|title=So abortion will be an issue in 2014. Where could it make a difference?|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-fix/wp/2013/07/08/so-abortion-will-be-an-issue-in-2014-where-could-it-make-a-difference/|accessdate=September 2, 2014|publisher=Washington Post|date=July 8, 2013}}</ref>\n\n=====Healthcare=====\nGrimm voted to repeal the [[Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act]] in the House, as he had promised during his campaign.<ref>[http://www.brooklyneagle.com/categories/category.php?category_id=31&id=40866 Brooklyn Eagle, Bay Ridge Eagle Brooklyn, NY :: daily paper in Brooklyn]{{dead link|date=April 2012}}</ref> Grimm was challenged as being \"hypocritical\" by several Democrats for enrolling in the congressional health-care plan.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tracy |first=Thomas |url=http://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/34/3/all_healthcarerepeal_2011_1_28_bk.html |title=Dems take on Grimm\u2019s \u2018job-killing canard\u2019 in health care debate |publisher=The Brooklyn Paper |date=January 20, 2011 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/2011/01/19/2011-01-19_rep_michael_grimm_takes_beating_from_fellow_congressmen_for_his_health_care_comm.html | location=New York | work=Daily News | title=Rep. Michael Grimm takes beating from fellow congressmen for his health care comments | first=Richard | last=Sisk | date=January 19, 2011}}</ref>\n\n=====Immigration=====\nGrimm has expressed support for immigration reform<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gay|first1=Mara|title=Michael Grimm Expressed Limited Support for Immigration Law Changes|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/metropolis/2014/04/29/michael-grimm-expressed-limited-support-for-immigration-law-changes/|accessdate=September 2, 2014|publisher=Wall Street Journal|date=April 29, 2014}}</ref> and was one of six Republicans to vote against an amendment that would have resumed deportation of \u201cDreamers.\u201d<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mascaro|first1=Lisa|title=GOP rejects Dream Act-like deportation deferrals|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2013/jun/06/news/la-pn-gop-rejects-deportation-deferrals-20130606|accessdate=September 2, 2014|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=June 6, 2013}}</ref>\n\n=====Israel=====\nGrimm made Israel a strong priority during his term. Grimm was appointed to the House Republican Israel Caucus in January 2011, serving as co-chair.<ref>{{cite web|last=Randall |first=Judy L. |url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2011/01/rep_michael_grimm_named_co-cha.html |title=Rep. Michael Grimm named co-chair of House Republican Israel Caucus |publisher=Staten Island Advance |date=January 31, 2011 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> In February 2011, as House Republicans were pushing for deep cuts in [[discretionary spending]], Grimm wrote a letter to [[Eric Cantor]] saying he would vote against any budget that would reduce foreign aid to Israel.<ref>{{cite press release |last= Danko |first = Carol |location = Washington |publisher= U.S. Congressman Michael Grimm |url=http://www.thestatecolumn.com/state_politics/new-york/rep-michael-grimm-stands-up-for-israel-opposes-cuts-to-aid/ |title= Grimm Stands Up for Israel; Opposes Cuts to Aid}}</ref> Grimm was also named chair of the House Republican Policy Committee's Task Force on Foreign Policy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2011/02/staten_islands_rep_grimm_named.html |title=Staten Island's Rep. Grimm named chair of GOP Policy Committee's Task Force on Foreign Policy |publisher=Staten Island Advance |date=February 16, 2011 |accessdate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> <!-- they appear to target many people - such a list belongs in that article, not in every BLP  The [[Democratic Congressional Campaign Committee]] (DCCC) targeted Grimm on his vote for [[Continuing resolution|spending cuts]] in the 2011 [[United States budget]]. The Brooklyn paper reported that Grimm's seat was widely-sought after as a potential win for Democrats in 2012.\n<ref>http://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/34/9/br_grimmcuts_2011_3_4_bk.html</ref> -->\n\n=====Syria=====\nGrimm opposed a military strike on the Assad regime in Syria, stating that \u201cI am no longer convinced that a U.S. strike on Syria will yield a benefit to the United States that will not be greatly outweighed by the extreme cost of war.\u201d<ref>{{cite news|last1=Blake|first1=Aaron|title=Republican congressman withdraws support for Syria strike|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/09/05/republican-congressman-withdraws-support-for-syria-strike/?wprss=rss_politics&clsrd|accessdate=September 2, 2014|publisher=Washington Post|date=September 5, 2013}}</ref>\n\n=====Fundraising allegations by Rabbi Pinto=====\nAccording to a January 27, 2012 article in the ''[[New York Times]]'', several followers of Orthodox Rabbi [[Yoshiyahu Yosef Pinto]] said Grimm's campaign had accepted questionable donations. According to the report, three of Pinto's followers said that Grimm or Ofer Biton, a top aide of Pinto's, had told them that the campaign would find a way to accept donations that were over the legal limit. Grimm stated, \"Any suggestion that I was involved in any activities that may run afoul of the campaign finance laws is categorically false and belied by my life of public service protecting and enforcing the laws of this country.\" <ref>{{cite news |last1=Cowan |first1=Alison Leigh |last2=Rashbaum |first2=William K. |title=Rabbi's Followers Cast Doubt on Congressman's Fundraising |date=January 27, 2012 |accessdate=September 18, 2013 |publisher=N.Y. Times |url= http://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/28/nyregion/rabbis-followers-say-money-given-to-grimms-house-race-broke-the-law.html}}</ref>\n\n=====Hurricane Sandy aid=====\nIn June 2013, Grimm stated that he believed water fees should be waived for survivors of [[Hurricane Sandy]] who had been displaced from their homes. Under New York City's Department of Environmental Protection rules, all homeowners are subject to a minimum charge of $1.19 per day, even if a home uses no water during a given period. Residents who had been displaced from their homes for long periods of time received water bills over $500 for damaged, vacant properties. Grimm called the bills \"ridiculous,\" stating \"That's $500 these people could use to replace a washer or dryer or refrigerator swept out to sea during Sandy.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Vigliotti|first1=Jonathan|title=Staten Island Sandy Victims Charged for Water in Vacant Homes|url=http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Water-Bills-Sandy-Staten-Island-Rep-Michael-Grimm-212630241.html|accessdate=July 24, 2014|publisher=NBC News|date=June 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Rep. Grimm To City: Stop Billing Sandy Victims For Water They Can\u2019t Use|url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2013/06/22/rep-grimm-to-city-stop-billing-sandy-victims-for-water-they-cant-use/|accessdate=July 24, 2014|publisher=CBS News|date=June 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\n=====Altercation with reporter=====\nOn January 28, 2014, [[NY1]]-TV political reporter Michael Scotto was interviewing Grimm in a balcony-hallway of the U.S. Capitol building, asking him about his thoughts on the recently concluded [[2014 State of the Union Address]]. He then tried to question Grimm about a campaign finance investigation. Grimm stated that he would only discuss the State of the Union speech, and not the investigation. As Scotto started to mention the investigation again, Grimm walked off. Scotto then turned to the camera and implied that Grimm didn't want to face the issue on-camera. Grimm then appeared to intimidate Scotto, saying that he would \"break (Scotto) in half,\" as well as threatening to throw Scotto over the balcony.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/01/29/us-usa-politics-grimm-idUSBREA0S0WM20140129|title=U.S. congressman apologizes for threatening to throw reporter over balcony|publisher=Reuters|date=January 29, 2014|accessdate=March 23, 2014|author=Thomas Ferraro}}</ref>\n\nGrimm issued a statement defending his behavior, saying that he was annoyed by what he called a \"disrespectful cheap shot\" from Scotto.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ny1.com/content/pages/202672/rep--grimm-threatens-ny1-reporter-following-state-of-the-union|title=Rep. Grimm Threatens NY1 Reporter Following State of the Union|publisher=[[NY1]]|date=January 28, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Campbell|first= Colin|title=Michael Grimm Threatens|publisher=Politicker|date=January 28, 2014|url=http://politicker.com/2014/01/michael-grimm-threatens-reporter-during-interview/}}</ref> The next day, Grimm contacted Scotto to offer an apology for his behavior, which Scotto deemed to be sincere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/ny1-reporter-michael-scotto-frightened-article-1.1595067|title=Rep. Grimm apologizes to NY1 reporter Michael Scotto|last1=Larson|first1=Leslie|date=January 29, 2014|website=nydailynews.com|publisher=New York Daily News|accessdate=January 29, 2014}}</ref> He also issued a written statement apologizing for his behavior, saying, \"I shouldn\u2019t have allowed my emotions to get the better of me and lose my cool.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ny1.com/content/news/202674/rep--grimm-apologizes-to-ny1-reporter-for-on-camera-threat|title=Rep. Grimm Apologizes to NY1 Reporter For On-Camera Threat|publisher=[[NY1]]|date=January 29, 2014}}</ref> An unnamed former staffer for Grimm and NY1-TV political director Bob Hardt reported that Grimm had behaved in a similar manner to other reporters on  previous occasions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nypost.com/2014/01/29/congressman-apologizes-for-threatening-reporter|title=Rep. Grimm sorry for threat against reporter|publisher=New York Post|date=January 29, 2014|accessdate=February 5, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ny1.com/content/politics/ny1_political_itch/202681/ny1-itch--a-grimm-tale-of-disunion-in-washington|title=NY1 ItCH: A Grimm Tale of Disunion in Washington|publisher=[[NY1]]|date=January 29, 2014|accessdate=February 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\n=====Flood insurance reform=====\nIn early 2014, Grimm and [[Bill Cassidy]] co-sponsored the Homeowner Flood Insurance Affordability Act. In March 2014, the bill was passed by the U.S. Senate and subsequently signed into law by President Obama. The law repealed exponential increases in flood-insurance rates for homeowners in flood-prone areas, preventing \"skyrocketing\" flood insurance premiums for 5.5 million Americans.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Durrett|first1=Clint|title=Obama signs bill into law preventing flood insurance rate hikes|url=http://www.wdsu.com/news/local-news/new-orleans/obama-signs-bill-into-law-preventing-flood-insurance-rate-hikes/25093406#!bkSDCP|accessdate=July 24, 2014|publisher=WDSU|date=March 21, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Wrobleski|first1=Tom|title=Senate passes flood insurance bill from Staten Island Rep. Michael Grimm by vote of 72-22|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2014/03/senate_passes_flood_insurance.html|accessdate=July 24, 2014|publisher=Staten Island Live|date=March 13, 2014}}</ref>\n\n=====Environmental views=====\nAccording to ''[[Politico]]'', in April 2014 Grimm became \"the first sitting House Republican to stop denying the science that humans cause climate change.\" Speaking about his views on global warming, Grimm stated: \"The majority of respected scientists say that it\u2019s conclusive, the evidence is clear. So I don\u2019t think the jury is out.\u201d<ref>{{cite news|last1=Goode|first1=Darren|title=Grimm\u2019s woes cast cloud on climate turnabout|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2014/04/michael-grimm-indictment-climate-change-106040.html|accessdate=July 24, 2014|publisher=Politico|date=April 25, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Harrison|first1=Timothy|title=Rep. Grimm endorses climate change science, dropping previous skepticism, after Hurricane Sand|url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2014/04/rep_grimm_endorses_climate_cha.html|accessdate=July 24, 2014|publisher=Staten Island Live|date=April 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Committee assignments====\n*'''[[United States House Committee on Financial Services|Committee on Financial Services]]'''\n**[[United States House Financial Services Subcommittee on Capital Markets and Government-Sponsored Enterprises|Subcommittee on Capital Markets and Government-Sponsored Enterprises]]\n**[[United States House Financial Services Subcommittee on Monetary Policy and Trade|Subcommittee on Monetary Policy and Trade]]\n**[[United States House Financial Services Subcommittee on Oversight and Investigations|Subcommittee on Oversight and Investigations]]\n\n====Caucus memberships====\n*Friends of Switzerland Caucus (Co-Chair)\n*House Republican Israel Caucus (Co-Chair)\n*House Oceans Caucus (Co-Chair)\n*[[United States Congressional International Conservation Caucus|International Conservation Caucus]]\n*Sportsmen's Caucus\n\n==Federal criminal investigation==\nIn August 2012, the office of the [[United States Attorney for the Eastern District of New York]] said it was investigating Grimm's 2010 campaign.<ref>{{cite news |title=Congressman's Report of Trip Is at Issue |last1=Cowan |first1=Alison Leigh |last2=Rashbaum |first2=William K. |publisher=N.Y. Times |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/09/nyregion/timing-of-grimms-report-on-expense-paid-cyprus-trip-questioned.html |date=August 8, 2012 |accessdate=September 18, 2013}}</ref> In November 2012, the [[House Ethics Committee]] decided to inquire into the campaign but agreed to \"defer consideration\" of it at the Department of Justice's request.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Cowan |first1=Alison Leigh |title=Ethics Panel to Scrutinize Congressman from S.I. |publisher=N.Y. Times |date=November 26, 2012 |accessdate=September 18, 2013 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/27/nyregion/ethics-panel-eying-finances-of-representative-michael-g-grimm.html}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2014, the FBI arrested Diana Durand<ref>{{cite web |title=New York Rep. Michael Grimm threatens reporter after being asked about fundraising allegations |date=January 29, 2014 |accessdate=January 30, 2014 |publisher=New York Daily News |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/new-york-rep-michael-grimm-threatens-reporter-asked-fundraising-allegations-article-1.1594857}}</ref> on charges that she had illegally donated more than $10,000 to Grimm's 2010 campaign. Durand allegedly gave the campaign $4,800, the legal limit, but then used [[straw donor]]s to donate more than $10,000 illegally. The FBI also charged Durand with lying to federal agents about the matter. Grimm denied any wrongdoing.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rashbaum|first=William K.|title=F.B.I. Arrests Fund-Raiser for Congressman|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/14/nyregion/fbi-arrests-fund-raiser-for-congressman.html?hp|accessdate=January 14, 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=Jan 2014}}</ref> In September 2014, Durand pleaded guilty to making illegal contributions to Grimm's 2010 campaign.<ref>[http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2014/09/texan_diana_durand_pleads_guil.html \"Diana Durand pleads guilty to making illegal contributions to GOP Rep. Michael Grimm's 2010 campaign,\" Staten Island Advance, September 3, 2014. Accessed November 3, 2014.]</ref>\n\nThe investigation, which originally focused on Grimm's 2010 fundraising, branched out to include Grimm's prior business dealings. On April 25, 2014, Grimm's attorney was advised by the U.S. Attorney's office that his client would be indicted on criminal charges related to Healthalicious.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/26/nyregion/indictment-expected-for-representative-michael-grimm.html|title=Indictment Expected for Grimm, Staten Island Congressman|last=Rashbaum|first=William|publisher=New York Times|date=April 26, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/25/politics/congress-grimm/index.html|title=Feds close to filing charges against Rep. Michael Grimm, officials say|author1=Evan Perez|author2=Shimon Prokupecz|publisher=CNN|date=April 25, 2014}}</ref> On April 28, prosecutors unsealed a 20-count indictment charging that Grimm and others concealed over a million dollars of the restaurant's sales and wages from both the U.S. federal government and the State of New York.<ref name=\"Clifford\"/> Grimm surrendered to the FBI that morning.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/rep-michael-grimm-facing-federal-charges-will-surrender-to-fbi-sources-say/2014/04/27/fd302426-ce33-11e3-b812-0c92213941f4_story.html?wpisrc=al_politics|title=Rep. Michael Grimm, facing federal charges, surrenders to FBI|publisher=The Washington Post|date=April 28, 2014}}</ref> Grimm pleaded not guilty to all charges and was released on $400,000 bond. He told reporters that he not only had every intention of fighting the charges, but also of staying in office and running for a third term.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2014/04/28/rep-michael-grimm-expected-to-surrender-to-face-federal-charges|title=Staten Island Rep. Michael Grimm Pleads Not Guilty To 20-Count Indictment|publisher=[[WCBS (AM)]]/[[WINS (AM)|WINS]]|date=April 28, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn December 23, 2014--less than two months after winning reelection--Grimm pled guilty to one charge of felony tax evasion.  He admitted to under-reporting Healthalicious' revenues by over $900,000 over four years and filing false tax returns based on that under-reported income.  He also admitted to using the under-reported receipts to pay restaurant expenses, as well as make under-the-table cash payments to employees.   As part of the plea bargain, the other charges were dropped.  However, he admitted to two of the offenses in the original indictment\u2014knowingly employing people ineligible to work in the United States and lying in a 2013 deposition.  Sentencing is scheduled for June 2015; he could face as much as 30 months in prison.<ref name=DailyNewsPlea>{{cite news|url=http://nydailynews.com/news/politics/rep-michael-grimm-pleads-guilty-felony-count-tax-evas-article-1.2054723|title=Rep. Grimm pleads guilty to felony count of tax evasion|work=New York Daily News|date=December 23, 2014}}</ref><ref>[https://www.scribd.com/doc/250884499/Grimm-Stipulation-of-Facts Copy of Grimm's allocution]</ref>\n\nGrimm admitted to making mistakes, but when a reporter asked him if he would resign, he said, \"Absolutely not.\"<ref name=DailyNewsPlea/>  However, on December 29, 2014, it was reported that after discussing the matter with House Speaker [[John Boehner]], Grimm had changed his mind and would decline to take his seat for a third term.  He will formally resign from Congress on January 5, 2015.<ref>http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/michael-grimm-reportedly-decided-resign-congress-article-1.2060152</ref> There will be [[New York's 11th congressional district special election, 2015|a special election]] to replace him in 2015.\n\nHad Grimm not resigned, his role in Congress would have likely been very limited.  Longstanding House rules state that a member convicted of a felony should not take part in floor votes or committee work until the [[United States House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct|House Ethics Committee]] reviews the matter.  Although there is no constitutional rule barring a convicted felon from voting, Boehner and the Republican leadership would have strongly discouraged Grimm from doing so, and the House Ethics Committee has indicated in the past that convicted felons can be disciplined if they do take part in committee or floor votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/RL33229.pdf|title=Status of a Member of the House Who Has Been Indicted For or Convicted of A Felony|author=[[United States House of Representatives]]}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGrimm lives on [[Staten Island]].<ref name=CQ/> He is single with no children.<ref name=fairytale/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sisterlinks|s=no|v=no|b=no|wikt=no|q=Michael Grimm}}\n*{{official website|http://www.grimm.house.gov/}}\n*[http://grimmforcongress.com/ Michael Grimm for Congress]\n*{{CongLinks | congbio = G000569 | votesmart = 127075 | opencong = 412451 | fec = H0NY13074 }}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{USRepSuccessionBox | state = New York | district = 13 | before = [[Michael McMahon]] | after = [[Charles B. Rangel]] | years = January 3, 2011 \u2013 January 3, 2013<br/>(Redistricted after the [[United States Census, 2010|2010 U.S. Census]])}}\n{{USRepSucc